3. Summary statistics derived from workflow-histories (Cardoen et al.)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Source: Cardoen, Mens, Decan (University of Mons). A dataset of GitHub
        Actions workflow histories. MSR 2024.
Zenodo DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.17301952
License: CC-BY-4.0
Use: numeric summary statistics (workflow-name frequencies, branch-name
     pattern frequencies) committed to `gh_distributions.toml`. No raw
     dataset content is redistributed.

4. Summary statistics derived from GHALogs (Moriconi et al.)
------------------------------------------------------------
Source: Moriconi, Durieux, Falleri, Troncy, Francillon. GHALogs: a
        large-scale dataset of GitHub Actions runs. 513k workflow runs
        across 2.3M individual steps over 116k workflows / 25k projects.
Zenodo DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.10154920
License: CC-BY-SA-4.0 (Share-Alike).
Use: summary statistics only (conclusion frequencies, Hawkes-process
     inter-arrival parameters per repo size class, per-event-type
     transition matrix). Numeric summaries are not derivative works in
     the typical Share-Alike sense; no raw GHALogs content is
     redistributed. If the waitbus project later embeds raw GHALogs
     content, the Share-Alike contagion must be re-evaluated.

